author: Nicholas Mccallum
title: Redback spider makes a meal out of baby brown snake in mechanics shop - Yahoo7
text:
Share Redback spider makes a meal out of baby brown snake in mechanics shop - Yahoo7 Mechanics in a northern Victorian workshop filmed a bold battle between a redback spider and baby brown snake with spoils going to an unlikely victor. Close Redback spider takes down baby snake in losing battle UP NEXT VIDEO Making an appearance at a Victorian factory, a baby snake was killed by a redback in a losing battle after workers tempted the spider into the attack. Source: Facebook/ North Vic Engines Redback spider takes down baby snake in losing battle 
The gripping video has been met with criticism after numerous viewers accused the workers who recorded the battle of sticking the reptile with a fishhook to stop slithering off on the arachnid. 
"We had a visit today from a baby snake," mechanics at North Vic Engines in Cobram wrote on Wednesday's Facebook post. 
"Lucky our pet redback found it and killed it for us!" The spider caught itself a snake. Source: Facebook/North Vic Engines Cobram 
Despite having the advantage of size and weight, the brown snake was outmatched by the relatively large spider that had strong webbing and knew how to use it. 
Once the snake was ensnared, the spider's venom made short work of it, delivering the "kill shot" before the mechanics got back to work. 
The video has been viewed 1.9 million times since it was posted, with many top comments accusing the engine mechanics in the border town of rigging the fight in favour of their pet spider. The baby brown snake was no match for the smaller spider. Source: Facebook/North Vic Engines Cobram 
Many accused the mechanics of putting a fishhook in the snake to stop it from escaping the spider's clutches. 
"Weak human beings using a fishing hook to bait snakes and entertain themselves," one person wrote. 
But business owner Brenton Maher denied the snake was leashed, telling 7 News Online there was no hook. Many viewers said the snake had a fishhook in its neck, preventing it from escaping. Source: Facebook/North Vic Engines Cobram 
"They're only little tiny things," he said of the baby brown. 
Two more baby snakes had been spotted since coming across the spider bait on Wednesday. 
To prove "the haters" wrong, the mechanics posted another video on Thursday morning showing another baby snake wrapped up well and truly in a spider's web. Close Snake caught in spider web UP NEXT VIDEO Denying claims that the spider and snake battle was staged, workers at North Vic Engines have released footage of another snake caught in a spider web at the same location. Source: Facebook/ North Vid Engines Snake caught in spider web
